<HEAD>Shultz Urges Strict Enforcement of Extradition Pacts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Secretary of State George P. Shultz called on
Wednesday for strict enforcement of extradition treaties to combat
terrorism.
   ``The more one country does it, the more other countries take
heart,'' Shultz told a group of business executives who are
concerned with security problems abroad.
   ``We need to support all of these elements that go with the rule
of law,'' he said. ``Extradition treaties are a big part of it, and
letting people see they will be extradited to the place where they
committed a crime. We have to stand by these things.''
   Shultz said applying extradition treaty is one way of sending a
message to terrorists that ``there's no place to hide.''
