<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Wendy's,0269</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Wendy's Posts Profit Gain In 3rd Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wendy's International Inc. said Wednesday its
third-quarter profit climbed 74 percent from a year earlier on a
slight rise in revenue.
   The fast-food restaurant company's net income for the quarter was
$8.7 million, or 9 cents per share, compared with $5 million, or 5
cents per share for the same quarter a year ago, the company
reported. Revenue was $273.7 million, up from $272.2 million.
   Systemwide sales _ the total sales from company and franchise
restaurants _ were $769 million for the quarter, an increase from
$742 million during the same quarter a year ago, the company said.
   Robert L. Barney, Wendy's chairman and chief executive, said the
company had effective purchasing agreements and better cost controls
at the restaurant level.
   For the first nine months of its fiscal year, net income was
$21.7 million, or 23 cents per share, versus $130,000 for the same
period last year. Revenue was $802.3 million, compared with $799.3
million a year earlier.
   Systemwide sales for the nine months totalled $2.2 billion,
compared with $2.1 billion the previous year.
   ``Our efforts to improve customer satisfaction and control
operating costs are producing the desired results,'' Barney said.
``I'm confident this will continue to be a strong turnaround years
for Wendy's.''
   The company made $4.5 million in profits in 1987 and lost $4.9
million the previous year.
   Wendy's said there were 3,760 Wendy's restaurants worldwide at
the end of the third quarter. There are 3,600 restaurants in the
United States.
